# Backend Conventions

> Backend only. Project-wide rules: `.cursor/rules/core/`.
> See also: `architecture.mdc` · `api.mdc`

## Barrel `index.ts` in Every Module

Each module (slice) within a layer must have a root `index.ts` that serves as its public API.

```
application/create-todo/
├── create-todo.use-case.ts
└── index.ts              # required — module public API

domain/todo/
├── todo.entity.ts
├── todo.repository.ts
└── index.ts
```

## Import Through Module Public API Only

Import from the module's public `index.ts` (`@/layer/module`). Never import internal files directly.

| Layer            | Public API path             | Example                     |
| ---------------- | --------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| `domain`         | `@/domain/[module]`         | `@/domain/todo`             |
| `application`    | `@/application/[module]`    | `@/application/create-todo` |
| `infrastructure` | `@/infrastructure/[module]` | `@/infrastructure/todo`     |
| `presentation`   | `@/presentation/[module]`   | `@/presentation/todo`       |

```ts
// ✅
import { CreateTodoUseCase } from '@/application/create-todo';
import { TodoRepository, Todo } from '@/domain/todo';
import { TodoController } from '@/presentation/todo';

// ❌ — deep file import
import { CreateTodoUseCase } from '@/application/create-todo/create-todo.use-case';
import { Todo } from '@/domain/todo/todo.entity';
```

If something is missing from the public API — add it to the module `index.ts`, do not import around it.

## Internal Barrels — Wiring Only

Use relative imports **only inside a module** when building its `index.ts`. External code must never import from internal files.

## Deep Imports — Exceptions Only

Reaching into module internals from outside is allowed only in:

- `main.ts`, `app.module.ts` (NestJS bootstrap and root module wiring)
- `tsconfig.json`, `nest-cli.json`

## Exports

Avoid `export default`. Use named exports and re-export via `index.ts`.

## Types and Constants

- Types and interfaces — `types.ts` within the module
- Domain constants — `constants.ts` in `domain/` modules
- API/presentation constants — `constants.ts` in `presentation/` modules
